+# SignalCore Roblox Studio Mode
+
+The Roblox Studio domain profile is **locked by default**. It is not a normal
+cross-platform Agent Skill entry point.
+
+## What can activate it
+
+Only an authorized external Roblox Studio bridge can activate the profile by
+presenting a short-lived signed session envelope containing:
+
+- Roblox Studio session ID
+- Place/project identity
+- project fingerprint
+- Roblox Studio process ID
+- explicit capability subset
+- issue and expiry timestamps
+- single-use nonce
+- HMAC-SHA256 signature
+
+## What cannot activate it
+
+- `--profile roblox_studio`
+- a Codex/Claude/Cursor/VS Code prompt
+- raw JSON without a valid signature
+- an expired or replayed envelope
+- a non-Roblox host or transport
+- a request for unapproved capabilities
+- a session without Roblox Studio process attestation
+
+## Pairing key
+
+The pairing secret is generated locally under SignalCore state and is never
+committed to the repository. The external bridge owns the pairing workflow.
+SignalCore exposes library functions but no CLI command that prints or accepts the
+secret.
+
+## Flow
+
+```text
+Roblox Studio
+    │
+    ▼
+Authorized Studio bridge
+    │ signed, short-lived, single-use envelope
+    ▼
+SignalCore profile loader
+    │ signature + process + project + capability + replay checks
+    ▼
+profiles/roblox_studio
+    │ TaskState → capability/model/engine/evidence/workflow policies
+    ▼
+External Roblox development engines
+```
+
+This is an activation and orchestration boundary, not a replacement for the Roblox
+Studio plugin, MCP, Luau compiler, Creator Store client, playtest environment,
+animation system, Blender worker, Digital Twin or migration lab.
+
+## Orchestration profile
+
+After authorization, `create_profile_runtime()` builds a fail-closed runtime with:
+
+- compound RobloxTaskState V2
+- 33-capability dependency graph
+- pinned engine and provider-independent model registries
+- measured role/capability certification
+- deterministic zero-model skip path
+- Evidence Ledger V3, project delta and artifact caches
+- multimodal evidence selection and Context Knapsack V2
+- workflow DAGs, checkpoints, repair and rollback policies
+- token/request/transfer/GPU/wall-time budgets
+- privacy firewall, strict response validators and cross-engine validation
+- telemetry, trace/replay and locked adaptive learning
+
+See `skills/signal-core/profiles/roblox_studio/ARCHITECTURE.md` and
+`BENCHMARK_RESULTS.md`.
+
+## Security limitation
+
+The profile gate prevents accidental and ordinary activation. It is not DRM and
+cannot protect against a local OS user who can read the pairing key or modify the
+source. Stronger local-adversary resistance belongs in the external bridge through
+OS keychain storage and native process attestation.
